test_presence_of_duplicates_in_result:
assert (3 == 3 and 3 == 3 and 2 == 3)
 +  where 3 = <built-in method count of list object at 0x732632bb8e80>([733])
 +    where <built-in method count of list object at 0x732632bb8e80> = [[1, 733], [1, 733, 1], [733], [733, 1], [1, 733], [1, 733, 1], ...].count
 +  and   3 = <built-in method count of list object at 0x732632bb8e80>([1, 733])
 +    where <built-in method count of list object at 0x732632bb8e80> = [[1, 733], [1, 733, 1], [733], [733, 1], [1, 733], [1, 733, 1], ...].count
 +  and   2 = <built-in method count of list object at 0x732632bb8e80>([733, 1])
 +    where <built-in method count of list object at 0x732632bb8e80> = [[1, 733], [1, 733, 1], [733], [733, 1], [1, 733], [1, 733, 1], ...].count
test_if_sublist_product_equals_number:
assert 1 == 733
 +  where 1 = <built-in function prod>([])
 +    where <built-in function prod> = math.prod
